What you need to know:

Rugby union's global governing body last October banned trans women from the elite women's game, citing fears of increased injury risksThe FFR's decision means it becomes the first sporting federation in France to give the green light for transgender players to take part in elite domestic competitionTrans women who have not undergone surgery and therefore are still in the process of transitioning from male to female will be able to play in all official FFR competitions provided they agree to undergo a minimum 12-month hormone treatment